<br>
Someone shouted in a zone I was in that there was a vox raid starting, and to /join the raid channel if you were interested. Out of sheer boredom, I joined just to silently watch. After realizing: this raid is doomed without someone to help, I decided to go.<br>
<br>
Having been a fan (and participee) of the Mootare Cowzerger Nagafen raids (god those were own, i miss Mutare &gt;&lt;, anyway) I learned that in a silly way, watching n00bs kill dragons was sort of fun.<br>
<br>
It is possible, to just do it with a pickup raid. Adding in a 60 shaman, 60 cleric, and 60 enchanter into the formula pretty much trivializes the encounter 100%, and somewhat gimpifies it. So out of sheer boredom, I went just to toss some Aegolisms on the raid. I bribed a shaman friend to come as well (boy it's amazing what slow does to making vox trivial, even if the shaman gets ported out after slow lands <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) and we had some fun watching newbies zerg a dragon.<br>
<br>
Mere enjoyment of seeing how we used to all suck at one point is worth it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In any case, it's something different. Something entertaining, and on a really bored day, it gives you something to do.<br>
<br>
That, and missing the Cowzerger raids was at least my incentive for going. <p><center>Rhaje, Level 60 Cleric<BR>
